Subject: [PATCH] docs: fix inconsistencies in documentation

- Generate-code-from-TypeSpec.md: fix incorrect pnpm install command
  (`npm install -g @pnpm` -> `npm install -g pnpm`; the `@pnpm` package
  does not exist on npm). Update Node.js prerequisite from "LTS versions"
  to "Node.js 20 or later" to match the repo engine requirement (>=20).

- Quickstart-on-how-to-write-tests.md: update Node.js prerequisite from
  "LTS versions" to "Node.js 20 or later". Update code examples in both
  Example 1 (RLC/purview) and Example 2 (HLC/monitor) to use the current
  vitest testing patterns instead of the outdated mocha/chai patterns:
  - Replace `import { assert } from "chai"` with vitest imports
  - Replace `import { Context } from "mocha"` with `VitestTestContext`
    from `@azure-tools/test-recorder`
  - Replace `new Recorder(context.currentTest)` with `new Recorder(ctx)`
  - Replace `beforeEach(async function(this: Context))` with
    `beforeEach(async (ctx) =>` arrow function pattern
  - Update import paths to use `.js` extensions (ESM convention)

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
